title: Ballet Art - From the Renaissance to the Present (Art Ebook).pdf
description:
1978 | Crown | Pdf | English | 144 pages | 0517534541 | 24.6 MB

Since the Renaissance, Ballet has provided artists with a unique source of inspiration. In this fascinating collection of illustrations, you find dance as well as social history merge in an original study of the rich relationship between ballet and the visual arts.The chapter titles are: Renaissance Spectacle, Ballet Into the Threatre, The Romantic Movement, The World of Degas, The Diaghilev Years, Modern Times and Modern Crimes
